First, we need the endpoints of segment $s_2$.  We know segment $s_1$ has endpoints (1, 2) and (7, 10). Translating $s_1$ 3 units to the right and 2 units down means adding 3 to the x-coordinate and subtracting 2 from the y-coordinate of each endpoint.

